Some Questions

String Pool vs Heap?

Pool stores literals
Heap stores objects created via new

+ vs concat
 + and Concat does the same, both will add only

 but in concat s1 means the original value won;t change but in + it will create a new object and assign it to s1

 means in + -> s1 = s1 + " World"; // creates a new object and assigns it to s1 , s1 has been mutated to point to the new object
    in concat -> s1.concat(" World"); // creates a new object but s1 still points to the original object, s1 is not mutated